As you can see on the output, ddccontrol cannot access /dev/mem.
So unless you already have done so, you need to re-run the ddccontrol=20
tool as root.

On debian-like systems :
LANG=3D LC_ALL=3D sudo ddccontrol -pcd

On other systems :
su - ;
LANG=3D LC_ALL=3D ddccontrol -pcd

Please post the result in reply to this message.

William

